eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are between 18 and 55 (inclusive) years of age at the time of signing the informed consent.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Healthy participant status
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are overtly healthy as determined by medical evaluation, including no clinically significant abnormality identified on physical examination or laboratory evaluation and no active clinically significant disorder, condition, infection, or disease that would pose a risk to participant safety or interfere with the study evaluation, procedures, or completion.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Body weight and BMI requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have a body weight within 50.0 and 100.0 kg (inclusive) and BMI within the range 19.0 and 30.0 kg/m2 (inclusive).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Sex and contraception requirements
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male: No contraception and barrier requirements needed. Female: Is not a woman of childbearing potential. Note: Study to include approx. 30% or more of each sex

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed consent capability
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are capable of giving signed informed consent, which includes compliance with the requirements and restrictions listed in the ICF and this protocol.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Nonsmoker status
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are stable nonsmokers for at least 3 months preceding the first administration of study intervention.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Medical conditions exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History or presence of clinically relevant respiratory, gastrointestinal, renal, hepatic, hematological, lymphatic, neurological, cardiovascular, musculoskeletal, genitourinary, immunological, dermatological, connective tissue, psychiatric (due to rare risk of hallucinations, agitation and activation of psychosis), and other diseases or disorders, and epilepsy, as determined by medical evaluation.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic liver disease exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Individuals with diagnosis of hemochromatosis, Wilson´s disease, alpha 1 antitrypsin deficiency, or any other chronic liver disease including Gilbert's disease will be excluded from the study. Prior history of cholecystectomy or splenectomy, and any clinically relevant surgery within 6 months prior to the first administration of study intervention.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Malignancy history exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of any malignancy.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Seizure history exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of seizures.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Psychiatric disease exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of pharmacologically treated psychiatric disease.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Infection history exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of chronic or recurrent acute infection or any bacterial, viral, parasitic or fungal infections within 30 days prior to Screening and at any time between Screening and admission, or hospitalization due to infection within 6 months prior to the first administration of study intervention.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Shingles history exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of shingles within 12 months prior to Screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Drug hypersensitivity exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of drug hypersensitivity (e.g. quinolones and ascertained or presumptive allergy/hypersensitivity to the active drug substance and/or formulation ingredients); history of serious allergic reactions leading to hospitalization or any other hypersensitivity reaction in general including contact hypersensitivity to ECG electrodes, which may affect the safety of the participant and/or outcome of the study per the Investigator's discretion.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Alcoholism or drug abuse exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of alcoholism or drug abuse within 2 years prior to the first administration of study intervention, or positive for drugs of abuse, nicotine/cotinine or alcohol by the laboratory assays conducted during Screening and Study Day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Tuberculosis exposure exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of residential exposure to tuberculosis, or a positive QuantiFERON® test within 4 weeks prior to or at the time of Screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Infectious disease testing exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Positive for a) hepatitis B surface antigen, hepatitis B core antibody, hepatitis C antibody, or human immunodeficiency virus I and II tests at Screening; b) SARS CoV-2 at Screening or Study Day -1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigator discretion exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Any condition, including findings in the laboratory tests, medical history (e.g. heart failure, hypokalemia, family history of Long QT Syndrome), or other Screening assessments, that in the opinion of the Investigator constitutes an inappropriate risk or a contraindication for participation in the study or that could interfere with the study's objectives, conduct, or evaluation.
